body:
Me, from the future: you can only ask me one serious question about the future. It can be who you marry, how many kids you have, what your career looks like..”


Me: *acts like I’m seriously thinking* ok…


Me: will Tj and Cyrus ever kiss?


Future me: really? That’s your serious question?


Me: look, I can worry about those other small details later, but RIGHT NOW I NEED TO KNOW IF-

title: Meetin' at the Malt Shop
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2RVI2lr

by myhoneybee

When the Goodman’s marriage is torn apart, Cyrus and his mother pack up their bags and retreat to Shadyside. In the midst of it all, Cyrus befriends Buffy Driscoll who shows him the ups and downs on the cusp of a new school year - all while enjoying a refreshment at family-owned Kippen’s Malts. Between soirees and several orders of tater tots, Cyrus struggles with a secret crush on the soda jerk that starts to become not-so-secret during a time that’s less than understanding. Will their puppy love be doomed?
Meetin’ at the Malt Shop delves into gay teenage romance set in 1959 and is loosely inspired by the Mickey Mouse Club Annette serials.

by myhoneybee

When the Goodman’s marriage is torn apart, Cyrus and his mother pack up their bags and retreat to Shadyside. In the midst of it all, Cyrus befriends Buffy Driscoll who shows him the ups and downs on the cusp of a new school year - all while enjoying a refreshment at family-owned Kippen’s Malts. Between soirees and several orders of tater tots, Cyrus struggles with a secret crush on the soda jerk that starts to become not-so-secret during a time that’s less than understanding. Will their puppy love be doomed?
Meetin’ at the Malt Shop delves into gay teenage romance set in 1959 and is loosely inspired by the Mickey Mouse Club Annette serials.

body:
3.12

This iconic long awaited episode is apparently called the Ex factor and because of Josh saying that the storyline in this episode creates a new story in the show and is something we all want I think it’s either one of two things:

A. Either after seeing Marty in the next episode Buffy needs to decide between him and walker which would create a new story between them and rebuilding Andi and Buffy’s friendship since their whole issue is over walker

Or

B. Or it has something to do with Tyrus for this I think either cy’s ex comes back or tj has an ex that is mentioned or something


I don’t think either of these are right just because if the cast list on imbd if it’s correct then I think gus is maybe Jonah (even though I don’t think he’s gay) Or tjs ex. ORRR amber and Jonah start hanging out again or something because those two are the only two non consistent characters that would make sense idek. I’ll have a better guess after 3.11

But I really feel like it might expose someone in the show as not being straight or exposing a really dark past because that’s honestly the only thing that could really spice up the show right now. But idk
